Class Order

java.lang.Object
com.vaadin.starter.bakery.backend.data.entity.AbstractEntity
com.vaadin.starter.bakery.backend.data.entity.Order
All Implemented Interfaces:
OrderSummary, Serializable
@Entity(name="OrderInfo") public class Order extends AbstractEntity implements OrderSummary
Entity representing a bakery order.

This entity manages order information including due dates, customers, items, pickup locations, and order history. The class implements OrderSummary to provide a summarized view of order data for performance optimization.

The entity uses named entity graphs for performance optimization:

  • ENTITY_GRAPTH_BRIEF - Loads basic order info with customer and location
  • ENTITY_GRAPTH_FULL - Loads complete order details including items and history

Note: The entity is mapped to "OrderInfo" table since "Order" is a reserved SQL keyword.

Since:
1.0
Version:

Bakery Application
